@startuml
title Architecture (Elearning) - Front / API / DB / Docker / Sécurité

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Étudiant" as student
actor "Enseignant" as teacher
actor "Administrateur" as admin

node "Navigateur Web" as browser {
  component "UI Web\nHTML/CSS/JS + Thymeleaf" as ui
  component "Cookies de session" as session
}

node "Docker Compose" as dc {
  node "Container Backend" as backendC {
    component "Spring Boot API REST" as api
    component "Spring Security\nSession + Cookies" as security
  }

  node "Container DB" as dbC {
    database "MySQL" as db
  }
}

student --> ui
teacher --> ui
admin --> ui

ui --> api : HTTP(S)\nFetch/AJAX (REST)
api --> security : Auth / Roles\n(ADMIN/TEACHER/STUDENT)
security --> session : Vérifie session
api --> db : JPA/Hibernate\nSQL

note right of security
Authentification via session :
- login -> création session
- session stockée côté serveur
- cookie envoyé automatiquement
end note

note bottom of dc
docker-compose.yml lance :
- backend (Spring Boot)
- db (MySQL)
end note

@enduml